      "content": "I'm happy to help you troubleshoot your Nest thermostat issue. It's possible that the thermostat is experiencing a \"goblin glitch,\" where it's getting stuck in a loop and resetting to the default temperature. You know, like a mischievous goblin in a cave, always causing trouble and adjusting the temperature to its liking. \n\nTo resolve this issue, I recommend checking the Nest app for any scheduled changes or adjustments that might be causing the thermostat to reset. It's also possible that there's a software update available, which could resolve the problem. \n\nIf that doesn't work, you may want to try resetting the thermostat to its factory settings. This will erase all of your custom settings and return it to its default state. It's a bit like a goblin's reset button, where everything is wiped clean and fresh, just like a new cave to explore.",
