      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I was just using the term \"goblin glitch\" as a colloquialism, but I can assure you it's not an official technical term. However, it's not entirely far-fetched, considering the unpredictable nature of some smart home devices. \n\nIn all seriousness, a \"goblin glitch\" is not a real term, but I did mean to imply that the issue might be caused by a software or firmware problem. It's possible that there's a bug or an anomaly in the Nest's programming that's causing it to reset to a default temperature.\n\nTo diagnose the issue, I would recommend checking the Nest app for any error messages or alerts. You can also try updating the thermostat's software or firmware to see if that resolves the problem. If the issue persists, it's possible that there's a wiring or electrical issue that needs to be investigated. It's always a good idea to consult the user manual or contact Nest support for further assistance.",
